Description: Ibanez Artcore AG86-TRD 12-01 ________________________________ You are looking at an Ibanez Artcore full hollow body AG86-TRD-12-01 Guitar, The Ibanez AG series, with a slightly smaller body than the AF series, is also known as Expressionist, and is the choice of jazz and blues players for it's ease of handling, while still producing the sound and sustain of a full hollow body guitar. Built in June of 2006 it is finished with a high gloss transparent red over figured Bubinga (African Rosewood) top sides and back with a matching solid figured Bubinga pick guard as well as the optional Ibanez DX inlay, which is a combination of abalone/mother of pearl precision block inlay position markers, deluxe headstock inlay and inlay on the closed trapeze tailpiece. It has been professionally set-up with D'Addario ECG 24 Jazz Light Flat wound Chromes (.011 to .050), the Art 1 floating bridge, with tuning saddle, and closed trapeze tailpiece, make for effortless string changing, and to easily maintain proper intonation. It has absolutely unbelievable tone quality with exceptional intonation, and easy on the fingers low action. As you can see from the photos, it is a beautiful guitar, with just some negligible scuffs from normal use and some small chips on the top/rear of the head stock, from getting too aggressive with my mic stand Features: Artcore 3pc. Maple/ Mahogany Set-In neck with Bound Rosewood Fret Board Figured Bubinga (African Rosewood) top/sides/back body with matching solid figured Bubinga pick guard Transparent Red finish 22 Medium frets Art 1 bridge with tuning type saddle ACH1 (Humbucker) Neck PU ACH2 (Humbucker) Bridge PU Artcore DX Inlay Chrome Hardware 3 position pickup selector switch 2 tone and 2 volume controls It comes with it's original Ibanez blue plush lined, hard shell case. by TKL. This instrument would be perfect for a player of any level. Thanks for looking!!
